# Split test and train sets

# Random forest classifier

Both the seats and DAUs were seen to be somewhat correlated and VIFs are relatively elevated. Let's test the model again by removing Seats.

Given the importance of Seats above, I doubt that the model will improve

churn_dummy_ns = churn_df_copy_no_ints_seats['Paid_status'].str.get_dummies()
churn_df_copy_no_ints_seats = pd.concat([churn_df_copy_no_ints_seats, churn_dummy_ns], axis = 1)
churn_df_copy_no_ints_seats.drop(columns=['Paying','Paid_status'],inplace=True)

X_no_seats = churn_df_copy_no_ints_seats.drop(['Churned'], axis=1)
y_no_seats = churn_df_copy_no_ints_seats['Churned']
X_train_ns, X_test_ns, y_train_ns, y_test_ns = train_test_split(X_no_seats, y_no_seats, test_size = 0.25, random_state = 0)

classifier_ns = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=0) 
classifier_ns.fit(X_train_ns, y_train_ns) 
predictions_ns = classifier_ns.predict(X_test_ns)
print(accuracy_score(y_test_ns, predictions_ns))
print(classification_report(y_test_ns,predictions_ns ))
